1.) Sign up for a new DigitalOcean account and claim the free $200 credit.
2.) Create a basic Ubuntu 20.04 droplet using a regular Intel CPU.
3.)Open the droplet console and install the required tools. Use the command: sudo apt install apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl software-properties-common -y
4.)Add the Docker GPG key: curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo apt-key add -
5.)Add the Docker repository using this code: sudo add-apt-repository \
"deb [arch=amd64] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu \
$(lsb_release -cs) \
stable"
6.) Verify the repo is set correctly using this command:apt-cache policy docker-ce
7.) Install docker using this code: sudo apt install docker-ce -y
8.) Install Docker Compose: sudo curl -L "https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/download/1.27.4/docker-compose-$(uname -s)-$(uname -m)" -o /usr/local/bin/docker-compose
9.) Apply executable permissions using: sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/docker-compose
10.) Make a wireguard Directory using this code: mkdir -p ~/wireguard/
11.) Create a config directory inside it using this code: mkdir -p ~/wireguard/config/
12.) Open the Docker Compose file for editing: nano ~/wireguard/docker-compose.yml
13.) Paste the following text: version: '3.8'
services:
  wireguard:
 container_name: wireguard
 image: linuxserver/wireguard
 environment:
PUID: 1000
PGID: 1000
TZ: America/Chicago
SERVERURL: 64.23.128.177
SERVERPORT: 51820
 PEERS: pc1,pc2,phone1
PEERDNS: auto
INTERNAL_SUBNET: 10.0.0.0
 ports:
 - 51820:51820/udp
 volumes:
- type: bind
source: ./config/
target: /config/
- type: bind
source: /lib/modules
 target: /lib/modules
restart: always
cap_add:
- NET_ADMIN
- SYS_MODULE
sysctls:
net.ipv4.conf.all.src_valid_mark: 1
14.) Move into the WireGuard directory using the code: cd ~/wireguard/
15.) Start the WireGuard container:docker-compose up -d
16.) Download the WireGuard mobile app.
17.) Tap the plus (+) sign and choose Scan from QR code.
18.) In the droplet console, run this to view the QR code: docker-compose logs -f wireguard
19.) Scan it with your phone, activate the VPN, and visit ipleak.net to confirm your IP address has changed.
20.) To connect a laptop. In the droplet console, navigate to your config directory and open the peer config file with nano.
21.) Copy the entire config contents.
22.) Create a new file in VS Code, paste the configuration, and save it.
23.) Install the WireGuard desktop app on your laptop and import the file you created.
24.) Activate the tunnel and check ipleak.net again to verify that the VPN is working.

